      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok that makes sense. so the light reactions are in the thylakoid and the calvin cycle is in the stroma, right? can u go into more detail about the calvin cycle specifically? like how does the CO2 actually get turned into glucose? i'm a bit lost on the actual steps of that part.",
